The article is a statement issued on April 23, 2020, wishing Muslims around the world a blessed and peaceful Ramadan. The statement acknowledges that Ramadan is a time for Muslims to renew and strengthen their faith through fasting, prayer, meditation, reading the Quran, and charitable deeds. The importance of prayer during challenging times is highlighted, and the statement expresses a hope that those observing Ramadan find comfort and reassurance in their faith. The statement concludes with the phrase "Ramadan Mubarak," which means "Blessed Ramadan" in Arabic.